{
  "texts": [
    "Let s ∈ E, i 0 ∈ s. If j 0 ∈ s then {j 0 } ∪ s = s ∈ E. If j 0 ∉ s then there exists t ∈ E i 0 ↓ j 0 such that s ⊂ t. Since i 0 ∈ s ⊂ t ∈ E i 0 ↓ j 0, it follows that j 0 ∈ t and consequently {j 0 } ∪ s ⊂∈ E. Again {j 0 } ∪ s ∈ E. This proves that δ i 0 j 0 is friendly in (I, E).",
    "◻ A.2 Foundation of a delegation on an invariant groundThe question arises about the interpretation of the notion of delegation (Subsection A.1) on the ground i.e., on the level of the P-foundation.",
    "We say that a p-structure (I, E) is σ-founded on the p-site a of ground A, if a ∈ PSITE(I, A) and σ a = E. In view of Corollary 1.5.9, any p-formation (I, E) where E is a I-simplicial complex, is σ-founded on a p-site a with ground A where E max ⊂ A ⊂ E, namely the canonical p-site associated to (I, A), ca(I, A), Indeed one has κ a = A and consequently σ a = κ ↓ a = E. The rest of this paragraph is devoted to understand what is specific about the σ-foundation of friendly delegations.",
    "In [1], the effectuation of a delegation ≡ δ i 0 j 0 is interpreted as the passage from E to δi 0 j 0 E ⊂ P(I ∖ {i 0 }); in particular, the delegating agent is put aside from the resulting p-formation.",
    "If the delegation is simplicial and a fortiori friendly, the resulting p-structure is (I, E -i 0)."
  ]
}